divs: Sighting DetailsFirst,I'm Chinese,my English is poor. The story: i was waked up by the noisy of somebody's ring tone outside. it's about 1:40, i saw a lightspot in the sky, i thought it might be a star, quickly i found it was impossible,for it's too light to the bad air in ShangHai. Then i thought it's a plane or satellite,it can't be a plane because it didn't move,i don't know if it's a satellite,so i took it a pic. before i took the pic,i thought it mast be a star or satellite an so on,when i saw the pic,i was confused,i really don't know what's on this pic. i suspected that,although i use the selfshot mode to take the photo,it took 15s to exposure,maybe the wind or something else swayed the camera. when i want to take another photo,the cloud hid the lightspot.
